1 c. Education and outreach related to the state's advanced technology resources,
2 including the advancement of engineering and technical readiness.
3 3. Each biennium, the research technology park shall develop a plan for the use of funds
4 received under this section, including industry matching requirements. The plan must
5 be approved by the industrial commission.
6 4. The research technology park may:
7 a. Select research topics and projects;
8 b. Enter into contracts or agreements with other institutions of higher education to
9 support the selected research topics and projects;
10 c. Enter into contracts or agreements with federal, private, and nonprofit
11 organizations to carry out the selected research topics and projects; and
12 d. Accept donations, grants, contributions, and gifts from any source to finance the
13 selected research topics and projects.
14 5. Annually, the research technology park shall report all research activities, product
15 development, and accomplishments to the industrial commission and the legislative
16 management. Upon request, the research technology park shall report to the
17 appropriations committees of the legislative assembly on the use of funding under this
18 section.
19 SECTION 2. TRANSFER - STRATEGIC INVESTMENT AND IMPROVEMENTS FUND TO
20 RESEARCH TECHNOLOGY PARK FUND. The office of management and budget shall transfer
21 the sum of $15,000,000 from the strategic investment and improvements fund to the research
22 technology park fund, during the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, and ending June 30, 2027.
